release bump notes

- do version bump work on a version-named branch, usually `release/<version>`
- bump both `VERSION` and `Support/Info.plist`
- keep `CFBundleShortVersionString` and `CFBundleVersion` aligned with `VERSION`
- update `Support/ReleaseNotes.md` with a short plain release note for the new version
- release publishing reads notes from `Support/ReleaseNotes.md` via `.github/workflows/build.yml`
- after a bump, run `swift build`
- generated local artifacts such as `Scout.dmg` and `.build/Scout.app` can be stale until `scripts/package-dmg.sh` or `scripts/package-app.sh` is run

workflow notes

- `pr-ready.yml` is triggered by `workflow_run`, so GitHub uses the workflow from `main`
- PR changes to `pr-ready.yml` affect readiness comments only after merge
- readiness comments should say `Runner macOS` for GitHub runner OS values

PR writing notes

- PR titles should be simple and truthful
- PR bodies should be short, plain, and accurate
- avoid heavy wording, filler, and section headers unless they add real clarity
- use backticks for filenames, commands, labels, and code identifiers
